'''Shirish Jagjivandas Panchal''', ({{lang-hi|शिरीष पंचाल}}; {{lang-gu|શિરિષ પંચાલ}} born 7 March 1943 in [[Vadodara]]),<ref name="gsp">{{cite web |url= http://gujaratisahityaparishad.com/prakashan/sarjako/savishesh/Savishesh-Shirish-Panchal.html|title= સાહિત્યસર્જક: શિરિષ પંચાલ|first= Chandrakant|last= Topiwala|publisher= Gujarati Sahitya Parishad|language= Gujarati|trans-title=Writer: Shirish Panchal}}</ref> is a [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]] critic, fiction writer, translator and editor who won the 2009 [[List of Sahitya Akademi Award winners for Gujarati|Sahitya Akademi Award for Gujarati language]] for his criticism ''Vaat Aapanaa Vivechan-ni''.<ref name="gsp"/><ref name="hindu">{{cite web |url= http://www.hindu.com/2009/12/24/stories/2009122462072200.htm|title= Poets dominate 2009 Sahitya Akademi Awards|date= 24 December 2009|publisher= The Hindu|location= Ahmedabad}}</ref> He done his Ph.D under Gujarati writer [[Suresh Joshi]]. He taught Gujarati language and literature at [[M. S. University]], [[Baroda]]. He edited ''Etad'', a Gujarati quarterly.<ref name="Pañcāla1998">{{cite book|author=Śirīsha Pañcāla|title=B.K. Thakore|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gZZjWzi42eUC&pg=PA60|accessdate=31 August 2017|year=1998|publisher=Sahitya Akademi|location=New Delhi|isbn=978-81-260-0373-0|page=60}}</ref>

