{{Infobox language |name=Zire |altname= Nerë, sîchë |nativename=''Sîshëë'' |region=[[New Caledonia]] |ethnicity= 19 (2009 census)<ref name=e18>{{cite web|url=https://www.ethnologue.com/18/language/sih/|title=Sîshëë|publisher=Ethnologue|edition=18th|accessdate=31 December 2017}}</ref> |extinct= 2006 |ref = <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.unesco.org/languages-atlas/index.php|title=UNESCO Atlas of the World's Languages in danger|website=www.unesco.org|language=en|access-date=2017-12-29}}</ref> |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Southern Oceanic languages|Southern Oceanic]] |fam5=[[New Caledonian languages|New Caledonian – Loyalties]] |fam6=New Caledonian |fam7=Southern |fam8=South Southern |fam9=Zire–Tiri |iso3=sih |glotto=zire1240 |glottorefname=Zire }}
'''Zire''' (Sîshëë), also known as ''Nerë'', is an extinct [[Oceanic languages|Oceanic language]] of [[New Caledonia]]. Speakers 4 (extinct since April 2006). Sometimes considered a dialect of Ajië
